=== Survivor & Culture Preservation ===
* Taliban:
During the Swat Operations Muhammad Parvesh Shaheen opposed [[Tehrik-i-Taliban Pakistan|Taliban]], being a prominent figure beaten, injured and damage caused to personal library by ''Taliban''.<ref name=librarian/><ref>[http://outsidethewire.armytimes.com/2011/03/01/bad-day-for-buddha-smashers/ Bad day for Buddha smashers], ArmyTimes, ''Published: March 1, 2011''</ref>

* Culture Preservation:
Buried personal archaeological remains in earth during the insurgency period for the preservation & latter on worked as volunteer with Italian Mission in the reconstruction of damage caused to the world known statue of [[Gautama Buddha|Lord Buddha]].<ref>[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jBj28aUODN4 Swat's Archaeological Treasures], YouTube, ''Published: March 14, 2011''</ref><ref>[http://tribune.com.pk/story/132215/tourism-in-swat-involve-private-sector-to-revive-industry/ Tourism in Swat: Involve private sector to revive industry, ] Express Tribune, ''Published: March 14, 2011''</ref><ref>[http://pakobserver.net/detailnews.asp?id=227778 Precious Kohistani Necklace], Pak Observer, ''December 24, 2013''</ref><ref>[http://www.uswat.edu.pk/index.php/office-of-the-social-work-program-represented-university-of-swat-in-three-days-swat-cultural-festival-held-on-may-30-31-june-1st-2014-at-swat-regency-hotel/ Office of the Social Work Program represented University of Swat in Three Days Swat Cultural Festival held on May 30-31, June 1st, 2014 at Swat Regency Hotel], University of Swat, ''Published: June 5th, 2014''</ref><ref>[https://alaiwah.wordpress.com/2011/02/16/taliban-have-left-swat-the-music-has-started-playing/ Taliban Have Left Swat & the Music Has Started Playing], ''Published: February 16, 2011''</ref>

